Youtube CyberSecurity Full Course-Edureka
	1) Types of Attacks:
		> Website Defacement
		> Buffer Overflow
		> Denial of Service
		> Distributed Denial of Service (DDOS)

	2) Penetration Testing:
		> Vulnerability Assessment
		> Create a detailed test report and suggest fixes to the bugs
		> Fixing the Vulnerabilites
		> Security Assessment

	3) Foot Printing: Gathering information of Target systems
		> Port Scans, Filters etc
		> Some tools: archive.org (Wayback machine), Netcraft

	4) Using DNS to get more information:
		> Internet registries (arin.net)
		> use of commands: whois <domain-name or IP>
						   dig <domain-name or IP>
		> DNS: Names to IP Addresses

	5) Finding Network Ranges:
		> host netflix.com
			this will return the IP address
		> dig -mx netflix.com

	6) Using Google for Reconnaissance (Google Hacking):
		> Using Google to target the things that you are looking for is a useful skill as an ethical hacker.
		> https://www.exploit-db.com/google-hacking-database

	7) NW Basics:
		> DARPA (Defence Advanced Research Project Agency)
		> IPv4 - 32 bit, IPv6: 128 bit
		> OSI and TCP/IP Model
		> UDP
		> Wireshark
		> Addressing Modes:
			> Unicast
			> Broadcast
			> Multicast
		> DHCP
		> ARP

	8) Cryptography:
		> Cipher-text (Encryption and Decryption)
		> DES (56 bits key size and block size of 64 bits) -> AES ( 3 different key sizes: 128/192/256 bits and block size of 128 bits)
		> Types of Cryptography: 
			Symmetric (Same keys) and Asymmetric (Different keys-Private and Public keys)
		> Symmetric:
			aescrypt -e -p god test.txt
			aescrypt -d -p god test.txt.aes

		> Asymmetric:
			Create file test.txt with some text in it.
			Generate a private key:
				openssl genrsa -des3 -out private.key 4096
			Generate a public key: 
				openssl rsa -in private.key -pubout -out public.key
			Encrypt the test.txt file using public.key:
				openssl rsautl -encrypt -pubin -inkey public.key -in test.txt -out encry-test.txt
											OR
				openssl pkeyutl -encrypt -pubin -inkey public.key -in test.txt -out encry-test.txt
			Decrypt the file using private.key:
				openssl pkeyutl -decrypt -inkey private.key -in encry-test.txt -out decry-test.txt 

	9) Certificates:
		> Create a Digital certificate
			> first create a private key:
				openssl genrsa -des3 -out -ca.key 4096
			> generating certificate:
				openssl req -new -x509 -days 365 -key -ca.key -out test.crt
			> viewing the certificate:
				openssl x509 -text -in test.crt

	10) Crytographic Hashing:
			> Examples of Hashing algorithms: md5, sha1
				md5sum test.crt







